meta:
  origin:
    producer: Alexander et al.
    title: 'Human appropriation of land for food: the role of diet'
    description: |-
      This dataset reports livestock conversion efficiencies as presented in Alexander et al. (2016), published in Global Environmental Change. It covers feed conversion ratios, protein efficiency, and energy efficiency for various animal products.

      "Feed conversion ratio" is defined as the quantity of feed inputs required to produce one kilogram of edible product, measured in kilograms of dry-matter feed per kilogram of edible weight product. Protein and energy efficiency are both measured as the percentage of protein or energy converted from feed to animal product.

      Original data sources used in the paper include Smil (2013), Opio et al. (2013), and Macleod et al. (2013).
    title_snapshot: Meat conversion efficiencies
    citation_full: 'Alexander, P., Brown, C., Arneth, A., Finnigan, J., and Rounsevell, M. D. (2016). Human appropriation of land for food: the role of diet. Global Environmental Change, 41, 88–98. Available at: http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0959378016302370?via%3Dihub#bib0330.'
    url_main: http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0959378016302370?via%3Dihub#bib0330
    date_accessed: '2026-03-05'
    date_published: '2016'
